    "actor_description": "Heat climbs my neck and face like a rash. My stomach drops-empty, sick-and my thoughts tighten into one ugly sentence: they saw that. I can feel my posture trying to fold in on itself, shoulders up, chin down, as if smaller would mean safer. My mouth goes dry. I want to say something-anything-to cover it, but every word feels like it'll make the spotlight brighter.",
